Plan for Improvements<BR>
================<BR><BR>

1. Blacksmithing.<BR><BR>

This is my grandmaster trade skill. My aim has always been to be able to make the finest Koada'Dal (High Elven) plate armour that can be made, namely, Imbued Enchanted Mithril Plate. <BR><BR>

After what feels like forever, and over 2000 combines using leather paddings, Fine Plate is now trivial. This skill can now only be further raised, toward the skill cap at 250, by making Cultural armour itself.<BR><BR>

Looking to Cultural then, the temper components for Moonlight Tempers, and the Tempers themselves, are what I am looking for now. So I would buy, if offered:<BR><BR>

Swirling Mist (25pp each)<BR>
Essence of Moonlight (20pp each)<BR>
Moonlight Temper (75pp each)<BR><BR>

2. Pottery.<BR><BR>

This has been stalled at 188 for a long while. There is only one way I can raise this to the maximum at 200 ... by making Imbued Idols. These are a nusiance to gather components for. To start with, I need Iron Oxide, Permafrost Crystals and White Lead, and that is just to make the glaze.<BR><BR>

I am finally working on gathering the components now. I have made 2 stacks of Divine Crystalline Glaze, and have commissioned a friendly enchanter to make some clarified mana for me. Progress soon, I hope. :) <BR><BR>

3. Tailoring.<BR><BR>

I've allowed this to sit quietly at 155 for some time now, while I work on Blacksmithing sand a little on Pottery component gathering. It can be raised to 158 fairly easily by gathering silk swatches, some vials of viscous mana from a friendly enchanter, and a large number of self-brewed Heady Kiolas, and making Wu's Fighting Tunics.<BR><BR>

After 158, it gets *very* hard, as only "Velious Tailoring" will do, and this is both very expensive and very slow, especially for a cleric. I have no plans to advance beyond 158 at this time.<BR><BR>

4. Baking.<BR><BR>

The road from 142 to 162 is hard. It needs Brownie Parts for everything. These are pain to get, and cleric s once again not a good class for killing brownies solo. I expect I will continue to be stalled here for some time at least.<BR><BR>

For information, beyond 162 is far worse even than this, as it requires dragon meat, and we all know how common that is! Even if I ever do raise this skill to 162, I doubt I will pass this until new recipes are introduced. <BR><BR></td></tr>
